<p>The <b>RSA</b> (<b>Rivest=E2=80=93Shamir=E2=80=93Adleman</b>) <b>cryptos=
ystem</b> is a family of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public-ke=
y_cryptography" title=3D"Public-key cryptography">public-key cryptosystems<=
/a>, one of the oldest widely used for secure data transmission. The <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Initialism" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Initialism">initialism</a> "RSA" comes from the surnames of <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ron_Rivest" title=3D"Ron Rivest">Ron Rivest</=
a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adi_Shamir" title=3D"Adi Shami=
r">Adi Shamir</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leonard_Adle=
man" title=3D"Leonard Adleman">Leonard Adleman</a>, who publicly described =
the algorithm in 1977.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-rsa1977tr_1-0" class=3D"reference=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RSA_cryptosystem#cite_note-rsa19=
77tr-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Gardner1977_2-0" class=3D"reference">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RSA_cryptosystem#cite_note-Gardner=
1977-2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-rsa_3-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RSA_cryptosystem#cite_note-rsa-3"><span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></s=
up> An equivalent system was developed secretly in 1973 at <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_Communications_Headquarters" class=3D"m=
w-redirect" title=3D"Government Communications Headquarters">Government Com=
munications Headquarters</a> (GCHQ), the British <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Signals_intelligence" title=3D"Signals intelligence">signals=
 intelligence</a> agency, by the English mathematician <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clifford_Cocks" title=3D"Clifford Cocks">Clifford Cock=
s</a>. That system was <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Classified_=
information" title=3D"Classified information">declassified</a> in 1997.<sup=
 id=3D"cite_ref-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/RSA_cryptosystem#cite_note-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>RSA is used in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_sign=
ature" title=3D"Digital signature">digital signature</a> such as <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Probabilistic_signature_scheme" title=3D"Pro=
babilistic signature scheme">RSASSA-PSS</a> or <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Full_Domain_Hash" title=3D"Full Domain Hash">RSA-FDH</a>,<sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-Bellare-Rogaway1996exactsigs_5-0" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RSA_cryptosystem#cite_note-Bellare-Rogaw=
ay1996exactsigs-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Aumasson2018seriouscrypto-=
rsasigs_6-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/R=
SA_cryptosystem#cite_note-Aumasson2018seriouscrypto-rsasigs-6"><span class=
