^{e}=3D(h^{d})^{e}=3Dh^{de}=3Dh^{ed}=3D(h^{e})^{d}\equiv h{\pmod {n}}.}"></=
span>
</p><p>The modular exponentiation for signing and verification is the same =
underlying mathematics as for decryption and encryption, but all the other =
details of padding scheme for secure <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Public-key_encryption" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Public-key encrypt=
ion">public-key encryption</a> and hashing for secure <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_signature" title=3D"Digital signature">digital =
signature</a> are different.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-pkcs1_33-1" class=3D"refere=
nce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RSA_cryptosystem#cite_note-pk=
cs1-33"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>32<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The use of a hash, first proposed in 1978 by <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_O._Rabin" title=3D"Michael O. Rabin">Michael O. R=
abin</a> in the related <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rabin_sign=
ature_algorithm" title=3D"Rabin signature algorithm">Rabin signature algori=
thm</a>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-rabin1978digsigs_37-0" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RSA_cryptosystem#cite_note-rabin1978di=
gsigs-37"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>34<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-rabin1979lcs-tr_38-0" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RSA_cryptosystem#cite_note=
-rabin1979lcs-tr-38"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>35<span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
and the security of the hash, is essential for security of the signature:<s=
up id=3D"cite_ref-djb2008rwsota_39-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RSA_cryptosystem#cite_note-djb2008rwsota-39"><span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>36<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a><=
/sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-bellare-rogaway1996exactsigs_40-0" class=3D"refere=
nce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RSA_cryptosystem#cite_note-be=
llare-rogaway1996exactsigs-40"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>37<span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> if Alice and Bob skipped the has=
h, and Bob checked for <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>s</i><sup><i>e</i></sup> =
=E2=89=A1 <i>m</i> (mod <i>n</i>)</span> instead, then anyone could forge t=
he signature <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>s</i> =3D 1</span> on the message <=
span class=3D"texhtml"><i>m</i> =3D 1</span>, or take two signed messages <=
span class=3D"texhtml">(<i>m</i><sub>1</sub>, <i>s</i><sub>1</sub>)</span> =
and <span class=3D"texhtml">(<i>m</i><sub>2</sub>, <i>s</i><sub>2</sub>)</s=
pan> from Alice and then forge a third by multiplication, <span class=3D"te=
xhtml">(<i>m</i><sub>1</sub><i>m</i><sub>2</sub>, <i>s</i><sub>1</sub><i>s<=
/i><sub>2</sub>)</span>, without knowledge of the private key.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Proofs_of_correctness">Proo=
fs of correctness</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-edit=
section-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?ti=
