italic;">k</span>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-42" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RSA_cryptosystem#cite_note-42"><span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">[</span>note 2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>To check whether two numbers, such as <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" s=
tyle=3D"font-style:italic;">m<i><sup>ed</sup></i></span> and <span class=3D=
"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span>, are congruent <span c=
lass=3D"texhtml">mod&nbsp;<i>pq</i></span>, it suffices (and in fact is equ=
ivalent) to check that they are congruent <span class=3D"texhtml">mod&nbsp;=
<i>p</i></span> and <span class=3D"texhtml">mod&nbsp;<i>q</i></span> separa=
tely.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-43" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/RSA_cryptosystem#cite_note-43"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
[</span>note 3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>To show <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>m<sup>ed</sup></i> =E2=89=A1 <i>m=
</i> (mod <i>p</i>)</span>, we consider two cases:
</p>
<ol><li>If <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>m</i> =E2=89=A1 0 (mod <i>p</i>)</spa=
n>, <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span> is a=
 multiple of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">p</s=
pan>. Thus <i>m<sup>ed</sup></i> is a multiple of <span class=3D"texhtml mv=
ar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">p</span>. So <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>m<=
sup>ed</sup></i> =E2=89=A1 0 =E2=89=A1 <i>m</i> (mod <i>p</i>)</span>.</li>
<li>If <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>m</i> =E2=89=A2 0 (mod <i>p</i>)</span>,
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e m^{ed}=3Dm^{ed-1}m=3Dm^{h(p-1)}m=3D(m^{p-1})^{h}m\equiv 1^{h}m\equiv m{\p=
mod {p}},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mi>m</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>e</mi>
            <mi>d</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>m</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>e</mi>
            <mi>d</mi>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>m</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>h</mi>
            <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
            <mi>p</mi>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>m</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>p</mi>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <msup>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>h</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo>=E2=89=A1<!-- =E2=89=A1 --></mo>
        <msup>
          <mn>1</mn>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>h</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo>=E2=89=A1<!-- =E2=89=A1 --></mo>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mspace width=3D"1em"></mspace>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
          <mi>mod</mi>
          <mspace width=3D"0.333em"></mspace>
