<dd>where we used <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fermat%27s_littl=
e_theorem" title=3D"Fermat's little theorem">Fermat's little theorem</a> to=
 replace <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>m</i><sup><i>p</i>=E2=88=921</sup> mod =
<i>p</i></span> with 1.</dd></dl></li></ol>
<p>The verification that <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>m<sup>ed</sup></i> =E2=
=89=A1 <i>m</i> (mod <i>q</i>)</span> proceeds in a completely analogous wa=
y:
</p>
<ol><li>If <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>m</i> =E2=89=A1 0 (mod <i>q</i>)</spa=
n>, <i>m<sup>ed</sup></i> is a multiple of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" sty=
le=3D"font-style:italic;">q</span>. So <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>m<sup>ed<=
/sup></i> =E2=89=A1 0 =E2=89=A1 <i>m</i> (mod <i>q</i>)</span>.</li>
<li>If <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>m</i> =E2=89=A2 0 (mod <i>q</i>)</span>,
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e m^{ed}=3Dm^{ed-1}m=3Dm^{k(q-1)}m=3D(m^{q-1})^{k}m\equiv 1^{k}m\equiv m{\p=
mod {q}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mi>m</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
