<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Proof_using_Euler's_theorem=
"><span id=3D"Proof_using_Euler.27s_theorem"></span>Proof using Euler's the=
orem</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brack=
et">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DRSA_cry=
ptosystem&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D14" title=3D"Edit section: Proof =
using Euler's theorem"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-b=
racket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Although the original paper of Rivest, Shamir, and Adleman used Fermat's=
 little theorem to explain why RSA works, it is common to find proofs that =
rely instead on <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euler%27s_theorem"=
 title=3D"Euler's theorem">Euler's theorem</a>.
</p><p>We want to show that <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>m<sup>ed</sup></i> =
=E2=89=A1 <i>m</i> (mod <i>n</i>)</span>, where <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>=
n</i> =3D <i>pq</i></span> is a product of two different prime numbers, and=
 <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">e</span> and <sp=
an class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">d</span> are positiv=
e integers satisfying <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>ed</i> =E2=89=A1 1 (mod <i=
>=CF=86</i>(<i>n</i>))</span>. Since <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"=
font-style:italic;">e</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font=
-style:italic;">d</span> are positive, we can write <span class=3D"texhtml"=
><i>ed</i> =3D 1 + <i>h=CF=86</i>(<i>n</i>)</span> for some non-negative in=
teger <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">h</span>. <=
i>Assuming</i> that <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic=
;">m</span> is relatively prime to <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"fo=
nt-style:italic;">n</span>, we have
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle m^{ed}=3Dm^{1+h\varphi (n)}=3Dm(m^{\varphi (n)})^{h}\equiv m(1)=
^{h}\equiv m{\pmod {n}},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
